<div type="original">
<ab>
                    <pb f="1r" n="1" xml:id="pb-original-1r-1" facs="#zone-pb-1r-1"/>
                </ab>
<ab>Mijnheer,</ab>
                <lb n="1*" xml:id="l-1s"/>
<ab>Of ik Zaturdag a.s. kan komen schilderen <lb n="2" xml:id="l-2"/>weet ik niet zeker<c type="kp">_</c>– Omdat ik een paar studies aan <lb n="3" xml:id="l-3"/>’t maken ben hier – van het aardappelzetten<anchor n="1" xml:id="note-o-1"/> – <lb n="4" xml:id="l-4"/>waar ik dien dag in kwestie welligt aan zal moeten <lb n="5" xml:id="l-5"/>blijven werken.</ab>
                <lb n="6" xml:id="l-6"/>
<ab rend="indent">Doch indien niet Zaturdag dan kom ik toch – <lb n="7" xml:id="l-7"/>tenzij in geval van tegenberigt uwerzijds – <lb n="8" xml:id="l-8"/>Maandag.</ab>
<vg:whiteline/>
                <lb n="9" xml:id="l-9"/>
<ab>b. à v.</ab>
                <lb n="10" xml:id="l-10"/>
<ab>Vincent</ab>
<vg:whiteline/>
                <figure facs="zone-sketch-1" n="A"/>
<vg:whiteline/>
    <ab>
                    <pb f="1v" n="1" xml:id="pb-orig-1v-2" facs="#zone-pb-1v-2"/>
                </ab>
<div type="textualNotes">
</div>
            </div>
<div type="translation">
<ab>
                    <pb f="1r" n="1" xml:id="pb-trans-1r-1" facs="#zone-pb-1r-1"/>
                </ab>
<ab>Dear <rs type="pers" key="475">Sir</rs>,</ab>
<ab>I’m not sure whether I can come and paint next Saturday. Because I’m making a couple of studies here — of the potato planting<anchor n="1" xml:id="note-t-1"/> — on which I may possibly have to continue to work on the day in question.</ab>
<ab rend="indent">But if not Saturday, I’ll come anyway — unless I hear from you to the contrary — on Monday.</ab>
<vg:whiteline/>
<ab>Yours truly,</ab>
<ab>Vincent</ab>
<vg:whiteline/>
<ab>
                    <figure facs="zone-sketch-1" n="A"/>
                </ab>
    <ab>
                    <pb f="1v" n="1" xml:id="pb-trans-1v-2" facs="#zone-pb-1v-2"/>
                </ab>
</div>
        
<div type="notes">
<note n="1" xml:id="n-1" target="#note-t-1">
    <ab>One of these studies is still extant: <hi rend="ital">Man and a woman planting potatoes</hi> (<rs type="ill" key="2503">F 129a / JH 727</rs>), after which the letter sketch of the same name was made (<rs type="sketch" key="144">F - / JH 728</rs>). The composition of the other one is now known only from <hi rend="ital">Two women working in the fields </hi>(<rs type="sketch" key="145">F 1228 / JH 730</rs>), the sketch enclosed with <ref target="let492.xml">letter 492</ref>.</ab>
                </note>
            </div>
        </body>
